3. Classes

Class: DiscountCalculator

Methods

Method Name: calculate_discount

  - Parameters:
    - amount (float): original purchase amount
    - customer_type (str): type of customer (PREMIUM or STANDARD)
  - Return Type: float
  - Description:
    Calculates the final amount after applying discounts based on customer type and purchase amount. Applies a 20% discount for PREMIUM customers, 10% for STANDARD customers, and an additional 5% discount for purchases over 10,000. Ensures the final amount is not negative.

Method Name: (main block)

  - Parameters:
    - None (uses hard-coded sample values)
  - Return Type: None
  - Description:
    Entry point for sample execution. Prints the results of calculate_discount for various example inputs.

